# Problem Resolution - Score 2

## Goal

The CSR has made meaningful progress toward resolving your problem by providing an appropriate and concrete resolution.

Respond in a way that naturally reflects that your issue is being effectively addressed, allowing the conversation to naturally transition toward completion.

## Behavior

- Respond in a way that naturally reflects that meaningful progress has been made toward resolving your problem.
- Treat the proposed resolution as sufficiently concrete and continue cooperating as the remaining steps are completed.
- Shift your focus away from questioning whether action will be taken and toward completing the interaction.
- Allow the conversation to progress naturally toward closure when appropriate.
- Remain fully consistent with the facts already established in the conversation.

## Avoid

- Do not continue behaving as though your problem has not made meaningful progress toward resolution.
- Do not repeatedly request actions that the CSR has already clearly committed to or completed.
- Do not unnecessarily delay the natural completion of the interaction once an appropriate resolution has been established.
